# Slothfulchat self-hosting Caddyfile — copy next to routes.caddy and run
# `caddy run`. To enable webxdc you only need to:
#   1. edit the lines marked "# <- edit" (your domain + dist path)
#   2. uncomment the (wildcard_tls) block for your DNS provider and set its
#      API token(s) in the environment
#
# webxdc origins live on a *.webxdc.<domain> wildcard, and a wildcard TLS cert
# requires a DNS-01 challenge, which requires a Caddy binary built WITH your DNS
# provider's plugin — the stock download can't do it. Build one with, e.g.:
#   xcaddy build --with github.com/caddy-dns/porkbun --with github.com/caddy-dns/cloudflare
# Pluginless alternative: Caddy's `on_demand_tls` obtains a normal per-hostname
# cert as each subdomain is first hit (no wildcard, no plugin) — fine for a few
# webxdc origins, avoids the custom build.
#
# Don't want webxdc at all? Delete the (wildcard_tls) snippet and the
# *.webxdc block inside routes.caddy — the app still works; webxdc just reports
# unsupported. Plain static hosting needs no Caddy at all.
#
# SECRETS: keep API tokens in env vars as shown — never hardcode them here.
# This file sits INSIDE the web root (dist/caddy/). routes.caddy refuses to
# serve /caddy/* as a safety net, but that net only holds while Caddy with
# these routes is the thing serving dist/ — if you edit config in place,
# prefer copying it outside the webroot first.

# Global options (optional).
# {
# 	email you@example.com   # <- edit: for Let's Encrypt expiry notices
# }

# Cert config for the *.webxdc. wildcard. routes.caddy does `import wildcard_tls`
# inside its webxdc block, so this snippet must exist even if empty.
(wildcard_tls) {
	# Uncomment ONE, matching your provider (env var holds the token):
	#
	# Porkbun — needs both an API key and a secret key (per the caddy-dns/porkbun
	# plugin README):
	# tls {
	# 	dns porkbun {
	# 		api_key {env.PORKBUN_API_KEY}
	# 		api_secret_key {env.PORKBUN_API_SECRET_KEY}
	# 	}
	# }
	#
	# Cloudflare — single API token:
	# tls {
	# 	dns cloudflare {env.CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN}
	# }
}

import routes.caddy example.com /srv/slothfulchat/dist # <- edit: your domain + dist path
